Structure.
Head (
Figs. 3–4
) with mandibular plates as long as or shorter than clypeus; lateral margins of mandibular plates with minute, triangular tooth in front of compound eyes (
Fig. 4
), sometimes absent (
Fig. 3
). Antennomeres from shortest to longest: I<IIa<IIb≤IV<III, scape (I) shortest and stoutest; remaining segments cylindrical and slender. Bucculae shorter than labiomere I, anterior apex with short, acute denticle. Labium reaching middle of ventrite IV, sometimes reaching posterior margin of ventrite IV (
Fig. 2
).
